      "note": "Or: \"allowed me to fall into error\". The term aghwahu denotes both \"he caused [or \"allowed\"] him to err\" or \"he caused him to be disappointed\" or \"to fail in attaining his desire\" (cf. Lane VI, 2304 f.). Since, in this case, the saying of Iblis refers to the loss of his erstwhile position among the angels, the rendering adopted by me seems to be the most appropriate."
